WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.600
Do you feel this way?

2
00:00:01.600 --> 00:00:04.160
When you communicate with AI,

3
00:00:04.160 --> 00:00:07.500
you often feel like you are talking to a wall.

4
00:00:07.500 --> 00:00:13.300
Today, we will talk about how to master the art of cooperation with deep AI

5
00:00:13.300 --> 00:00:16.700
so that you can really get the result you want in your heart.

6
00:00:16.700 --> 00:00:20.440
OK, let's cut into a painful point that many people have encountered.

7
00:00:20.440 --> 00:00:25.000
When you are using AI tools, you don't know why you will be stuck.

8
00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:28.460
You see, everyone should not be unfamiliar with this kind of picture.

9
00:00:28.460 --> 00:00:31.920
This is not just a cold technical error message.

10
00:00:31.920 --> 00:00:34.000
I think it's more like a metaphor

11
00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:38.060
that perfectly describes the feeling of failure of communication with AI.

12
00:00:38.060 --> 00:00:40.420
You clearly know what you want,

13
00:00:40.420 --> 00:00:44.320
but AI can't get to your point.

14
00:00:44.320 --> 00:00:48.160
The sense of failure is just like the error message on the screen.

15
00:00:48.160 --> 00:00:51.420
It tells you directly that our communication is cut off.

16
00:00:51.420 --> 00:00:55.660
That's right, this unconnected line is the core problem we have to solve today.

17
00:00:55.660 --> 00:00:58.020
How do we break away from this kind of communication gap?

18
00:00:58.020 --> 00:01:03.520
Don't worry, the good news is that there is really a system that can help us push this wall.

19
00:01:03.520 --> 00:01:08.280
This solution does not require you to learn more complex and difficult instructions.

20
00:01:08.280 --> 00:01:13.380
It is actually a process, a concept called DD loop.

21
00:01:13.380 --> 00:01:18.720
Its core spirit is to communicate with AI, not to finish the instructions and be fine.

22
00:01:18.720 --> 00:01:21.320
It is a process of coming back and forth.

23
00:01:21.320 --> 00:01:24.520
You first describe what you want as clearly as possible.

24
00:01:24.520 --> 00:01:26.280
AI will give you a result.

25
00:01:26.280 --> 00:01:30.680
Then you have to play your judgment to identify the good and bad of this result.

26
00:01:30.680 --> 00:01:34.740
Finally, adjust your description at the beginning according to your identification.

27
00:01:34.740 --> 00:01:36.840
You see, this is a loop.

28
00:01:36.840 --> 00:01:42.880
So the goal of this loop is not just for AI to spit out a good answer.

29
00:01:42.880 --> 00:01:52.780
The real goal is to create some results that you can't even imagine by working with AI.

30
00:01:52.780 --> 00:01:55.380
This is the most powerful place.

31
00:01:55.380 --> 00:01:57.680
How does this loop work?

32
00:01:57.680 --> 00:02:00.280
Let's break it into two parts.

33
00:02:00.280 --> 00:02:03.140
The first half is your description of AI.

34
00:02:03.140 --> 00:02:06.880
The second half is your identification of AI's output.

35
00:02:06.880 --> 00:02:08.740
Whether it's description or identification,

36
00:02:08.740 --> 00:02:12.540
there are three key core elements to do them well.

37
00:02:12.540 --> 00:02:14.540
Let's call it three P.

38
00:02:14.540 --> 00:02:18.380
OK, let's look at the first part, the art of description.

39
00:02:18.380 --> 00:02:23.440
That is to say, how to talk to AI at the beginning to make your needs clear.

40
00:02:23.440 --> 00:02:26.500
This is really more important than you think, 100 times more important than you think.

41
00:02:26.500 --> 00:02:30.500
OK, three P, the first P is product, which is output.

42
00:02:30.500 --> 00:02:35.440
The point here is to be specific, specific, specific.

43
00:02:35.440 --> 00:02:38.200
You can't just tell him to write an article for me.

44
00:02:38.200 --> 00:02:39.500
It's too vague.

45
00:02:39.500 --> 00:02:42.340
You have to tell him what the format of this article is.

46
00:02:42.340 --> 00:02:44.700
Is it a blog article or an official report?

47
00:02:44.700 --> 00:02:47.900
Is the style lively and interesting or serious and professional?

48
00:02:47.900 --> 00:02:50.040
How many words are the length?

49
00:02:50.040 --> 00:02:51.940
How deep are the details?

50
00:02:51.940 --> 00:02:54.000
Make these clear.

51
00:02:54.000 --> 00:02:57.800
Next, the second P, process, which is the process.

52
00:02:57.800 --> 00:02:59.300
This is super cool.

53
00:02:59.300 --> 00:03:01.840
You don't just tell AI what you want.

54
00:03:01.840 --> 00:03:04.300
You can also guide him how to do it.

55
00:03:04.300 --> 00:03:06.640
It's like you're teaching him to think.

56
00:03:06.640 --> 00:03:09.940
For example, you can ask him to do market analysis first.

57
00:03:09.940 --> 00:03:11.900
Find three main groups of customers.

58
00:03:11.900 --> 00:03:15.200
Finally, make marketing suggestions for each group.

59
00:03:15.200 --> 00:03:17.140
Give him a framework, a step.

60
00:03:17.140 --> 00:03:19.440
The quality of the result will be much better.

61
00:03:19.540 --> 00:03:22.400
Okay, the third P, performance.

62
00:03:22.400 --> 00:03:25.540
This is more like setting AI's personality.

63
00:03:25.540 --> 00:03:27.940
What kind of attitude do you want him to cooperate with you?

64
00:03:27.940 --> 00:03:31.200
Do you want him to talk about the essence or the long story?

65
00:03:31.200 --> 00:03:34.500
Do you want him to challenge your ideas like a strict coach?

66
00:03:34.500 --> 00:03:37.640
Or like a gentle partner who keeps encouraging you and supporting you?

67
00:03:37.640 --> 00:03:39.800
You can set these.

68
00:03:39.800 --> 00:03:43.300
Okay, I've finished the first half of the description.

69
00:03:43.300 --> 00:03:46.440
When you use these three P to clarify the needs,

70
00:03:46.440 --> 00:03:48.640
AI will give you his answer.

71
00:03:48.640 --> 00:03:51.900
Next, let's move on to the second half of our cycle.

72
00:03:51.900 --> 00:03:54.240
It's also a very important step.

73
00:03:54.240 --> 00:03:55.940
The skill of identification.

74
00:03:55.940 --> 00:03:58.300
The skill of identification is actually

75
00:03:58.300 --> 00:04:00.940
to use the three P you just described

76
00:04:00.940 --> 00:04:03.800
as a check list.

77
00:04:03.800 --> 00:04:06.940
So first, identification output.

78
00:04:06.940 --> 00:04:07.940
Look back.

79
00:04:07.940 --> 00:04:10.200
Did he give you the right format?

80
00:04:10.200 --> 00:04:12.040
Is the style what you want?

81
00:04:12.040 --> 00:04:14.340
Is the length in line with the requirements?

82
00:04:14.340 --> 00:04:16.500
These things need to be checked one by one.

83
00:04:16.500 --> 00:04:19.000
Next, identification process.

84
00:04:19.000 --> 00:04:20.240
This is very important.

85
00:04:20.240 --> 00:04:22.000
Don't just look at the final answer.

86
00:04:22.000 --> 00:04:25.300
You have to think about how AI got this answer.

87
00:04:25.300 --> 00:04:28.500
Did he follow the steps you gave him step by step?

88
00:04:28.500 --> 00:04:31.640
Do you think the analysis method he used is reasonable?

89
00:04:31.640 --> 00:04:32.840
If the process is wrong,

90
00:04:32.840 --> 00:04:35.200
even if the result looks like it's okay,

91
00:04:35.200 --> 00:04:37.960
there may be blind spots that you can't see.

92
00:04:37.960 --> 00:04:39.940
Finally, identification performance.

93
00:04:39.940 --> 00:04:41.340
This is very intuitive.

94
00:04:41.340 --> 00:04:44.460
Just feel your cooperation experience.

95
00:04:44.460 --> 00:04:47.820
Do you think the AI way of talking to you is helpful?

96
00:04:47.820 --> 00:04:51.100
Will it be too talkative or a bit out of the question?

97
00:04:51.100 --> 00:04:52.820
If it feels wrong, it's okay.

98
00:04:52.820 --> 00:04:56.960
This is where you can adjust the next time you describe it.

99
00:04:56.960 --> 00:04:59.900
So when you put the description and identification

100
00:04:59.900 --> 00:05:02.960
and their three P together,

101
00:05:02.960 --> 00:05:06.100
you get a super powerful new ability.

102
00:05:06.100 --> 00:05:08.860
Let's go through a complete process.

103
00:05:08.860 --> 00:05:13.200
The first step is to use three P to produce process performance

104
00:05:13.200 --> 00:05:15.800
to clearly describe your needs.

105
00:05:15.800 --> 00:05:18.300
The second step, after the AI gives you something,

106
00:05:18.300 --> 00:05:22.260
you use the same three P to identify its quality.

107
00:05:22.260 --> 00:05:23.300
The third step,

108
00:05:23.300 --> 00:05:24.800
based on your identification result,

109
00:05:24.800 --> 00:05:28.840
give it feedback to correct the description at the beginning.

110
00:05:28.840 --> 00:05:31.200
This brings out the most important step four.

111
00:05:31.200 --> 00:05:32.740
Add you in.

112
00:05:32.740 --> 00:05:36.300
Your expertise, your experience, your judgment.

113
00:05:36.300 --> 00:05:37.660
Remember,

114
00:05:37.660 --> 00:05:39.500
AI is just your secondary driver.

115
00:05:39.500 --> 00:05:42.000
The steering wheel is still in your hands.

116
00:05:42.000 --> 00:05:43.160
So did you find it?

117
00:05:43.160 --> 00:05:44.260
What we're talking about today

118
00:05:44.260 --> 00:05:48.060
is far beyond the so-called singing or system engineering.

119
00:05:48.060 --> 00:05:51.960
This is actually training a new kind of critical thinking.

120
00:05:51.960 --> 00:05:56.820
What you're learning is how to work with a completely different intelligent body,

121
00:05:56.820 --> 00:06:01.300
how to guide it, evaluate it, and create value with it.

122
00:06:01.300 --> 00:06:04.560
This is a necessary ability in the future.

123
00:06:04.560 --> 00:06:05.700
Before we end,

124
00:06:05.700 --> 00:06:09.120
I want to leave a question for everyone to think about.

125
00:06:09.120 --> 00:06:10.060
For you,

126
00:06:10.060 --> 00:06:12.360
in the whole D-D cycle,

127
00:06:12.360 --> 00:06:14.960
which level do you think is more challenging for you?

128
00:06:14.960 --> 00:06:19.220
Is it the front that needs to figure out how to describe the thoughts in your mind

129
00:06:19.220 --> 00:06:21.660
or the back that needs to accurately identify

130
00:06:21.660 --> 00:06:23.900
whether what AI gives you is good or not?

131
00:06:23.900 --> 00:06:25.660
There is no standard answer to this question.

132
00:06:25.660 --> 00:06:26.700
But if you figure it out,

133
00:06:26.700 --> 00:06:29.320
you may find the key to your future training,

134
00:06:29.320 --> 00:06:32.320
which is also the starting point for you to truly master this superpower.
